Moody's Investors Service Inc said itdowngraded 1.7 billion dlrs of debt of Bankers Trust New YorkCorp, lead bank Bankers Trust Co and other subsidiaries.    It said the slate of key competitors in Bankers Trust'sprincipal markets shifted as the bank repositioned itself intothe global institutional markets. Moody's said the substantialnew capital committed to these markets, and the size of directcompetitors, increased the uncertainty of future performance.    Cut were the parent's senior and guaranteed debt to Aa-3from Aa-2 and subordinated debt to A-1 from Aa-3 and the leadbank's long-term debt and deposits to Aa-1 from Aaa. Reuter&#3;